§7§oThis gate lets you time redstone pulses and signals.

The gate has a clock input, a reset input, a running output, and an end output.

The clock for the state cell can be changed by right clicking.

When signal enters the clock input, the running output will produce a redstone signal for the amount of seconds specified in the clock. 

At the end of the specified time, the end output will pulse.

The state cell can be reset with a signal from the reset side.

The reset input is the side with the clock hand.

The clock input is the side with a redstone line that's next to the clock hand.

The running output is the side with a redstone line that's opposite to the clock hand.

The end output is the side with a redstone torch.
